New Records: Victor Wembanyama joined Hakeem Olajuwon and Andrei Kirilenko as the only NBA players to achieve a 5×5 more than once.
Key Match Events: Victor Wembanyama amassed 25 points, nine rebounds, seven assists, five blocks, and five steals.
Chris Paul contributed 19 points, 10 assists, seven rebounds, and two steals.
Collin Sexton led Utah with 16 points.
John Collins added 14 points and 11 rebounds.
Harrison Barnes scored six points for the Spurs in a 16-2 run to open the second half.
San Antonio forced Utah into 12 turnovers in the third quarter.
The Spurs outscored the Jazz 30-14 in the third quarter, turning a six-point halftime deficit into a 77-67 lead going into the final quarter.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Jazz played without leading scorer Lauri Markkanen due to back spasms.
Utah led 53-47 at halftime but fell apart in the third quarter en route to a fifth straight loss to begin the season.
The Jazz are the only winless team remaining in the NBA.
Former San Antonio player Patty Mills sparked his new team with all nine of his points off the bench in the first quarter.
Utah started two rookies due to injuries: Kyle Filipowski and Cody Williams.
